    <h2><strong>What is the economic appeal of bitcoin?</strong></h2>
    <br />
    <p>
      Bitcoin is a denationalized currency – it is not bound by the economy of a
      single government, region, or entity. It is thought to be a mix between a
      traditional currency and a commodity (such as gold), possessing the
      desirable traits of durability, divisibility, portability, high liquidity,
      and low transaction costs. For some, it represents the prototype for a
      global currency and for others, its volatility provides appeal as a
      speculative asset.
    </p>
    <br />
  </div>

